                {
                    "stage": "initial",
                    "content": "A 52-year-old female is on day +22 following an allogeneic hematopoietic stem cell transplant (allo-HSCT) from a matched unrelated donor for acute myeloid leukemia (AML). She is receiving tacrolimus and mycophenolate mofetil for GVHD prophylaxis. Her tacrolimus trough level this morning is 8.2 ng/mL (target 5-15 ng/mL). She has been progressing well with neutrophil engraftment (ANC 1,200/μL). Today she reports a new diffuse, erythematous, maculopapular rash involving her face, palms, and trunk. She estimates it covers about 30% of her body surface area. She also notes mild, intermittent loose stools (4 episodes, approximately 600 mL total in 24 hours) and mild nausea. Vital signs: T 37.8°C, HR 92 bpm, BP 118/72 mmHg, RR 18/min. Labs: WBC 3,400/μL, ANC 1,200/μL, hemoglobin 9.1 g/dL, platelets 42,000/μL, total bilirubin 1.8 mg/dL, AST 62 U/L, ALT 58 U/L, albumin 2.8 g/dL, creatinine 0.9 mg/dL.",
